This paper describes the design process behind the contact card user interfkce in Claris Organizer 2.0. This was a situation where traditional UI elements were insufllcient to satisfy the design’s requirements. High-fidelity prototypes were developed, iterated and tested against competing designs. Standards end guidelines had to be broken to achieve the design’s objectives. Despite having more fields and more functionality, the resulting design was smaller, fhster, and preferred by users.